<h2>Overview</h2>

<p>Virginia presents exceptional opportunities for both solar energy generation and efficient HVAC systems, making it an ideal state for homeowners looking to reduce energy costs and environmental impact. With an average of 4.6 peak sun hours per day and electricity rates averaging 11.9¬¢ per kWh, Virginia offers favorable conditions for solar panel installations that can generate significant long-term savings. The state's primary utility provider, Dominion Energy, serves over 2.6 million customers and has been expanding renewable energy programs, creating additional opportunities for residential solar adoption.</p>

