<h2>Virginia Incentives & Rebates</h2>

<p>Virginia offers several attractive incentives and rebates for solar panel and HVAC system installations, making these investments more financially accessible for homeowners. The most significant benefit is the federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC), which allows homeowners to deduct 30% of the cost of installing a solar energy system from their federal taxes. This credit applies to the total system cost, including equipment, installation, and associated expenses, with no cap on the credit amount. The 30% rate is available through 2032, making now an ideal time for solar investment.</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Federal 30% Solar Tax Credit:</strong> The ITC provides a dollar-for-dollar reduction in federal income taxes equal to 30% of the total solar system cost. For a \$20,000 system, this translates to \$6,000 in tax savings. The credit can be carried forward to future tax years if it exceeds current tax liability, and it applies to both residential and commercial installations.</li>
<li><strong>Virginia Solar Equipment Sales Tax Exemption:</strong> Virginia exempts solar energy equipment from state sales tax, saving homeowners approximately 5.3% on equipment costs. This exemption applies to solar panels, inverters, mounting systems, and battery storage components, potentially saving hundreds to thousands of dollars depending on system size.</li>
<li><strong>Dominion Energy Solar Programs:</strong> Dominion Energy offers net metering for solar customers, allowing excess energy production to be credited at retail rates. The utility also provides rebates for energy-efficient HVAC systems, including \$300-600 rebates for qualifying heat pumps and \$50-150 rebates for programmable thermostats.</li>
<li><strong>Local Utility Rebates:</strong> Many municipal and cooperative utilities in Virginia offer additional rebates for solar and HVAC installations. Northern Virginia Electric Cooperative (NOVEC) provides solar rebates up to \$1,200, while Rappahannock Electric Cooperative offers heat pump rebates up to \$400.</li>
<li><strong>Property Tax Exemption:</strong> Solar energy systems are exempt from local property tax assessments in Virginia, meaning the added home value from solar installation won't increase property tax bills. This exemption can save hundreds of dollars annually in property taxes.</li>
</ul>

